892 Sec. 24. (NEW) (Effective October 1, 2026) (a) As used in this section,
893 "artificial intelligence system" means any machine-based system that,
894 for any explicit or implicit objective, infers from the inputs such system
895 receives how to generate outputs, including, but not limited to, synthetic
896 digital content.
897 (b) Each employer that serves written notice on the Labor
898 Department pursuant to 29 USC 2102(a), as amended from time to time,
899 shall disclose to the department, in a form and manner prescribed by
900 the Labor Commissioner, whether the layoffs that are the subject of such
901 written notice are related to the employer's use of an artificial
LCO 29 of 30

Substitute Bill No. 435
902 intelligence system or another technological change.
903 (c) Any application for unemployment benefits shall include a
904 question concerning whether an applicant's unemployment is due to an
905 employer's use of an artificial intelligence system.
